titlestmt.titleproper: Commonwealth Fund records, Reports of the General Director/President, SG 1, Series 31
A Guide to the Commonwealth Fund records, Reports of the General Director/President, SG 1, Series 31 FA303

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2021-11-01 00:35:56 -0400.

did.unittitle: Commonwealth Fund records, Reports of the General Director/President, SG 1, Series 31

physdesc.extent: 36 document boxes and 1 record storage box.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Barry C. Smith served as General Director of the Commonwealth Fund, 1920-1947. During this period the reports were officially titled as Report of the General Director to the Directors of the Commonwealth Fund. Beginning in 1948, the offical title became known as Report of the President and Staff to Directors of the Commonwealth Fund.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use note
userestrict.p: Reproduction/duplication of archival items is routinely provided in accordance with "fair use." If the RAC does not hold copyright for an archival collection, or items within a collection, it is the user's responsibility to contact the copyright holder, or make a fair effort to do so, prior to publication.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Standard archival processing was conducted by Robert Battaly, Assistant Director, Head of Processing, Rockefeller Archive Center in February 2014, and Richard Torres, Assistant Archivist, Rockefeller Archive Center in August 2014, to arrange and describe the material and enable access. Further archival processing, primarily to address the preservation and conservation needs of the records, will be conducted at a later date, as necessary.
